<span id="freeTextContainer3121456617814755424">If I ever need to wrap my mind and my heart in a warm blanket of comfort, I pick Rosamunde Pilcher&apos;s book, where the girl will always end up with the right man, and where all misfortunes swiftly turn into good luck and happiness. Unrealistic, but cosy and comforting. And with good psychological portraits of the characters. These stories are no different, each one of them could&apos;ve been turned into a full blown novel, they are like little teasers of books that will never be written or that could&apos;v</span>
  <span id="freeText3121456617814755424" style="display:none">If I ever need to wrap my mind and my heart in a warm blanket of comfort, I pick Rosamunde Pilcher's book, where the girl will always end up with the right man, and where all misfortunes swiftly turn into good luck and happiness. Unrealistic, but cosy and comforting. And with good psychological portraits of the characters. These stories are no different, each one of them could've been turned into a full blown novel, they are like little teasers of books that will never be written or that could've been written if Pilcher was still alive... 3.5*</span>
