<span id="freeTextContainer1889194316853900545">I&apos;m not usually one for reading short stories, but it was a busy week and I wanted something I could easily dip in and out of. Rosamunde Pilcher didn&apos;t disappoint me. I wasn&apos;t a fan of &quot;The Shell Seekers&quot;, but I found novels like &quot;Coming Home&quot; and &quot;September&quot; hard to put down. So it was with these short stories. There were a couple that I found very predictable and two that I wouldn&apos;t care if they disappeared from the book. But the majority drew me in and I didn&apos;t want them to end - I cared abou</span>
  <span id="freeText1889194316853900545" style="display:none">I'm not usually one for reading short stories, but it was a busy week and I wanted something I could easily dip in and out of. Rosamunde Pilcher didn't disappoint me. I wasn't a fan of "The Shell Seekers", but I found novels like "Coming Home" and "September" hard to put down. So it was with these short stories. There were a couple that I found very predictable and two that I wouldn't care if they disappeared from the book. But the majority drew me in and I didn't want them to end - I cared abou the characters and wanted to know what happened to them next. In other words, I wished that they had simply been the first chapter of a full-blown book. </span>
